org.xlbean

Class XlBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>
        • org.xlbean.XlBean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>

    public class XlBean
extends java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>
    Data store class.

    Basic concept of this library is to read or write any value on excel sheet as String. This class is to hold this string value with it's name as map.

    This class extends HashMap and overrides put(String, Object) to limit types of object it can hold. This class can have following classes as value of map.

    • XlBean
    • XlList
    • SingleValue
    • String
    If you want to put any value other than the types above, use set(Object) method which converts any type of object, including Map, List or any other custom classes, to XlBean suitable type.

    Other methods defined in this class are utility to convert Map to other format easily.

      • beanOf

        public <T> T beanOf(java.lang.String sourceKey,
                    java.lang.Class<?> destinationClass)
        Returns the object of destinationClass filled with the contents mapped from a Map retrieved by sourceKey.

        If an object retrieved by sourceKey is null or not Map instance, then it returns blank instance of destinationClass.

        Mapping from Map of sourceKey to instance of destinationClass is key to property mapping. Refer to BeanConverter for further detail.

        Parameters:
        sourceKey -
        destinationClazz -
